This paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also mentions Bayesian methods and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses exploration-exploitation trade-offs, which are relevant to robotics and control systems, falling under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions regret bounds, which are relevant to decision-making and optimization, falling under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.DS.
